text: Vicente Aguilar Carmona (born April 10, 1970 in Valencia) is a 5-per-team football player from Spain. He has a disability: he is blind. He played 5-per- team football at the 2004 Summer Paralympics. His team finished third after they played Greece and, won 2-0. He was a member of the national team in 2013 and competed in the European Championships. == References == Category:Spanish footballers Category:Living people Category:1970 births Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for Spain Category:2004 Summer Paralympics Category:People from Valencia Category:Spanish 5-per-team footballers
